<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>So as I understand it the invited guest showed up and covered until the Reso people wandered in at various times then the &quot;guest&quot; where summarily booted out. How nice. <br>
<br>
I only responded to this post because of the condescending attitude of the Reso people especially the guild leader. If Reso is so uber why bother to invite others, or to be ever so helpful to these poor guilds that are worthless without you<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Resolution had no problems with guests until recently . Now that we are backflagging our guild for Elemental Planes access--new faces have suddenly popped up who want to raid with us. We do now get tells from people who dont want to join resolution, dont want to help resolution, just want flags.<br>
<br>
Jhary and Nakath are NOT llate-coming flag-seekers nor were *ANY* of our guests at Rallos Zek. Im only saying this because the guild's more open attitude towards guests has shifted as a result of flag seekers, and this may have contributed to the misunderstanding.<br>
<br>
I did announce in the raid channel that there was a game-enforced capacity of 72 people allowable in our raid and listed the priority of various constituents including the possibility of requiring raid status for members over other constituents. I understand that sometimes announcements in channels can go unnoticed. <br>
<br>
The main purpose of our guest program is to enable people to see how Resolution raids and see if they want to join. <br>
<br>
Esoteric Order is the main exception to this, as Resolution and EO have had a history of helping one another. Some of us were guests at their Kael raid the other day, I know I was. One of the issues that came up was that Nakath (EO) brought Jhary and Yethuy (Prophetic Order). This is not to say that PO was unwelcome, only to say that there was some confusion as to their status.<br>
<br>
In any case the responsibility of the Guild Leader is to manage Allied Guilds guests and the responsibility of the Recruitment officer to manage potential applicant guests. As guests of guests, I believe Jhary and Yethuy were in neither category and were lost in the shuffle. Managing the hardest encounter the guild has ever faced with 72+ plus raiders is very hard.<br>
<br>
At the time of their guest joining, I believe I communicated only my hesitation to Nakath, but did not clearly define the guilds policy. Also, as the officer who initiated the raid and managing the guest program (the Guild leader was not on at the time) I will take responsibility for not clearly communicating our policies at the time. Had I done so, neither of the Prophetic Order guests would likely have come. My Apologies.<br>
<br>
Corrina<br>
Recruitment officer<br>
